The Guessing Game is a simple Python-based interactive game where the user tries to guess the number of occurrences
of a randomly selected letter in a given text.
The game provides hints to guide the player toward the correct answer.

Features:
- Randomly selects a letter from a predefined list.
- Asks the user to guess how many times the letter appeared in the text.
- Provides dynamic hints based on how close the guess is.
- Keeps track of the number of attempts.
- Ensures valid input handling (prevents non-integer entries.
